==English==

===Etymology===
[[File:Kakashi2.jpg|thumb|Scarecrows in a [[rice paddy]] in [[Japan]].]]

From {{compound|en|scare|crow}}. Replaced original {{m|en|shewel}} from {{noncog|enm|sheweles}}, of unclear origin but probably from an unattested {{w|Old English}} form, composed of {{compound|ang|scȳn|-els}} ({{noncog|ang|scīewels}}). Compare {{cog|gml|schūwelse}} and {{cog|gmh|schiusel}}. See further at {{m|en|shy}}. Another replaced term for the thing was {{m|en|shoy-hoy}}, perhaps imitative of the cry of crows.

